{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"598c","heading":"Easements for hurricane and storm damage reduction projects","label":"598c Easements for hurricane and storm damage reduction projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/ch12/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","“Secretary” DefinedSecretary means the Secretary of the Army, see , set out as a note under .section 1002 of div. A of Pub. L. 118–272section 2201 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"such certification and construction are in compliance with the terms of the report of the Chief of Engineers for the project and the applicable project partnership agreement; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"fulfill the Federal responsibility with respect to the project or carry out any required nourishment of the project under the existing project authorization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"carry out repair and rehabilitation of the project under ; andsection 701n of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fa%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide any other relevant Federal assistance with respect to the project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Disclosure","label":"b Disclosure","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For any project for hurricane storm damage risk reduction, or a proposal to modify such a project, that is authorized after , for which a perpetual easement is required for Federal participation in the project, the Secretary shall include in the report of the Chief of Engineers for the project a disclosure of such requirement.January 4, 2025","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Management","label":"c Management","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To the maximum extent practicable, the Secretary shall, at the request of the non-Federal interest for a project for hurricane storm damage risk reduction, identify and accept the minimum real estate interests necessary to carry out the project, in accordance with .section 598b of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Hurricane and storm damage reduction project implementation","label":"d Hurricane and storm damage reduction project implementation","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"During the 2-year period beginning on , notwithstanding any requirement of the Secretary for a covered project to comply with the memorandum of the Corps of Engineers entitled “Standard Estates – Perpetual Beach Nourishment and Perpetual Restrictive Dune Easement” and dated , the Secretary shall carry out each covered project in a manner consistent with the previously completed initial construction and periodic nourishments of the project, including repair and restoration work on the project under .January 4, 2025August 4, 1995section 701n(a) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Covered project defined","label":"2 Covered project defined","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Brevard County, Canaveral Harbor, Florida – Mid Reach.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Brevard County, Canaveral Harbor, Florida – North Reach.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Brevard County, Canaveral Harbor, Florida – South Reach.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s598c/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs598c%2Fd%2F2%2FD","sourceRelea